{"id":14881827,"mediaExerciseId":"8e7ac37c-8066-4880-b15e-df7828cd1b3b","exerciseName":"11","chapterName":"23","chapterTitle":"Enterprise Risk Management","groupId":612487,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":787,"solutions":[{"id":6004899,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will compare the difference between transaction exposure and economic exposure.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"**Transaction exposure** affects a single transaction of the party. This type of exposure is due to the changes in the rates in different markets. \n\nOn the other hand, **economic exposure** is a long-term exposure of a company to the risk of changing prices that are related to the economy. This affects the valuation of the company as a whole instead of just a single transaction.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":213,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b3083609b70f54910f7eb31dddd9eda2/7943c086fe0a3bb99e7e245d5545956d/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":108,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b3083609b70f54910f7eb31dddd9eda2/7943c086fe0a3bb99e7e245d5545956d/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**Transaction exposure** can be hedged more easily since it is easier to find terms to hedge a single transaction rather than the value of a whole company. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b3083609b70f54910f7eb31dddd9eda2/6b2c42543550046d8a21efb5350004ff/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/11/b3083609b70f54910f7eb31dddd9eda2/6b2c42543550046d8a21efb535000